ABOUT

  Cantera is a group of programs for X11

COPYRIGHT

  Morten Hustveit 2006, 2007, 2008, 2009

CONFIGURATION

  The path of the configuration files are ``.cantera/config'' and
  ``.cantera/config.c''

  Options in ``.canterea/config'':

    terminal.history-size <history-size>
    terminal.font <font-path>
    terminal.font-size <font-size>
    terminal.palette <palette>

  Example Palettes
  ================

    ANSI: "000000 1818c2 18c218 18c2c2 c21818 c218c2 c2c218 c2c2c2 686868 7474ff 54ff54 54ffff ff5454 ff54ff ffff54 ffffff" 


  The C programming language is used for ``.cantera/config.c.  The
  configuration is compiled automatically by cantera-wm when it starts.  For
  configuration to work at all, you need GNU GCC installed.  On Debian systems,
  you can install this using ``apt-get install build-essential''.

  Here's an example configuration file:

    #include <cantera-config.h>

    void handle_hotkey(int ch)
    {
      switch(ch)
      {
      case 'b': launch("cantera-term"); break;
      case 'l': launch("xlock -erasemode no_fade"); break;
      case 'i': launch("iceweasel"); break;
      }
    }

  If you'd like to compile the configuration file yourself (for example to
  verify that there are no syntax errors), run:

    gcc -x c -fPIC -std=c99 ~/.cantera/config.c -shared -o ~/.cantera/config-`uname -m`.so
